Date: 1993-03-11

Title: The universality of the shift of the Chern-Simons parameter for a

general class of BRS invariant regularizationsAuthors: G. Giavarini, C.P. Martin and F. Ruiz Ruiz

Comments: phyzzx, 7 pages (no figures)

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B314 (1993) 328-332

We consider a biparametric family of BRS invariant regularization methods ofSU(N) Chern-Simons theory (the parameters defining the family taking arbitraryvalues in $\RR^2$) and show that the shift $k\to k + sign(k) N$ of theChern-Simons parameter $k$ occurs for arbitrary values of the family definingparameters. This supports irrefutably the conjecture that the shift of $k$ isuniversal for BRS invariant regulators.